        <h2>About me</h2>
        <p class="normal-text white">I fell in love with programming way back in the 80s after my introduction to the Apple IIe and Apple BASIC. I've been writing code personally and proffesionally ever since.</p>
        <p class="normal-text white">After 16 years of developing mainframe software, which turned out to not be a great career choice, I rebooted my career and switched to developing for the web. I consider myself to be primarily a back-end developer as this more closely resembles my previous experience but I do enjoy working on front-end code as well.</p>
        <p class="normal-text white">I intend to keep coding and learning as long as there is code to be written and new things to learn or until the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Technological_singularity" style="color: white; text-decoration: underline">singularity</a>.</p>
      </div>

